(1) The Board shall control and manage the activities of the Service and for such purposes it shall— (a) provide suitable facilities for the education and training of members of the Service and ensure that a proper portion of the time of the members of the Service is spent on such education and training; (b) provide employment by establishing, equipping, managing and maintaining establishments in Zambia where members of the Service shall work and be accommodated; (c) provide for the proper organisation of the Service ; (d) recruit members of the Service ; and (e) be responsible for the welfare, control and direction of members of the Service .
